COmmands : 
    - npm init
        - Creates a package.json file, interactive command




Package.json :
     - Contains info about the project
     - "Scripts" attribute lets you write commands more easily, for example to start a Node server
        - For standard commands (e.g. start), npm <standardcommand> is OK
        - For custom commands, npm run <customcommand>


Packages : 
    - Core node packages (fs, http, etc.)
    - 3rd party packages (not incluided in Node)
    - Available in npm repository
    - Install using npm install <mypackage>
    - Option "--save-dev" installs as dev dependency (not used for production deployment)
    - Option "-g" installs globally (not in node_modules)
    - Upon install, edits package.json with the installed package
